FME Online Output Processing — Future Work and Known Limitations
================================================================

This file tracks known issues, planned improvements, and future extensions
for the FME (Full Model Emulation) online output processing infrastructure.

STATUS: Production-ready for MPAS-O and MPAS-SI analysis members.
        ELM and MOSART wrappers are namelist-ready scaffolds pending
        full history system integration.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
PRIORITY 1: Required Before Full Production Deployment
------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. MAP FILE GENERATION
   - Generate ESMF/TempestRemap weight files for all component grids
   - EAM: ne30pg2 -> 1x1 (or target resolution)
   - MPAS-O/SI: oEC60to30 or oRRS18to6 -> 1x1
   - ELM: same as EAM if using same grid
   - MOSART: r05 -> 1x1
   - Store in E3SM inputdata repository for reproducibility

2. ELM FULL INTEGRATION
   - Connect elm_fme_derived_register() to histFileMod field registration
   - Connect elm_fme_derived_update() to driver timestep loop
   - Connect elm_fme_vcoarsen_register() and _update() similarly
   - Requires understanding ELM's bounds/filter patterns for hist_addfld1d
   - Reference: how ELM's existing histFileMod works with field pointers

3. MOSART FULL INTEGRATION
   - Connect rtm_fme_derived_register() to RtmHistFlds integration
   - Connect rtm_fme_derived_update() to Rtmrun timestep
   - Wire field data access from RunoffMod/rtmCTL state variables

4. MPAS-O HORIZONTAL REMAPPING INTEGRATION
   - The shared shr_horiz_remap_mod is available but not yet wired
     into the MPAS-O analysis members
   - Need wrapper: mpas_ocn_fme_horiz_remap.F in src/shared/
   - Challenge: MPAS decomposition (indexToCellID) differs from
     EAM chunk-based decomposition
   - The analysis member streams would need to write to the remapped
     grid instead of native MPAS grid

5. MPAS-SI HORIZONTAL REMAPPING INTEGRATION
   - Same as MPAS-O but for sea ice grid
   - May share the same map file if ocean and sea ice use same mesh

------------------------------------------------------------------------
PRIORITY 2: Improvements for Better Production Use
------------------------------------------------------------------------

6. MPAS-O DEPTH COARSENING: GENERIC FIELD SUPPORT
   - Currently hardcodes temperature, salinity, velocityZonal,
     velocityMeridional, layerThickness
   - The config_AM_fmeDepthCoarsening_fields namelist is parsed but
     not used for dynamic dispatch
   - Should loop over field names and use mpas_pool_get_array to
     fetch arbitrary fields by name

7. MPAS-O VERTICAL REDUCE: GENERIC FIELD SUPPORT
   - Currently computes only built-in fields (OHC, FWC, KE)
   - The config_AM_fmeVerticalReduce_fields and _methods namelists
     are defined but generic reduction not yet implemented
   - Should support user-specified tracer/diagnostic field reduction

8. MPAS-SI: ADDITIONAL DERIVED FIELDS FOR ACE
   - Air stress components (FA_X, FA_Y) with vector rotation from
     MPAS model coordinates to geographical (east/north)
   - Reference: mpas_seaice_geographical_vectors.F for rotation pattern
   - Sea surface fraction / wet mask from ocean static data

9. STREAM OUTPUT FREQUENCY CONFIGURABILITY
   - MPAS analysis member output intervals are set in Registry XML
     (default daily). For production, may want 5-daily for ocean.
   - Can override via streams.ocean_forward in SourceMods/src.mpaso/
   - Consider adding namelist options for output interval

10. FILL VALUE / MISSING VALUE ATTRIBUTES
    - Registry XML variables do not specify missing_value attributes
    - The Fortran code uses fillValue = 1.0E34 but NetCDF files
      won't recognize this as missing without _FillValue attribute
    - Add missing_value="1.0e34" to Registry var definitions
    - Or use MPAS's standard missing value mechanism

11. SINGLE PRECISION CONSISTENCY
    - MPAS stream output uses precision="single" (float32)
    - EAM cam_history uses default precision (double)
    - For FME training, float32 is preferred for all components
    - Verify EAM horiz_remap output uses single precision

