------------------------------------------------------------------------
NOTES ON ARCHITECTURE
------------------------------------------------------------------------

- Shared modules (share/util/shr_*.F90) are pure computation with no
  I/O, MPI, or component dependencies. This is by design.
- Component wrappers handle decomposition, field lookup, and history
  system integration. Each is thin (~200-400 lines).
- MPAS components use the Analysis Member pattern; EAM/ELM/MOSART use
  their respective history/namelist infrastructure.
- The shr_vcoarsen_mod is coordinate-agnostic: works with pressure
  (atmosphere), depth (ocean), or soil depth (land).

